      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t5-1",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "5-1",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t5-1-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-1-0"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t5-1-1"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "partial derivative of internal energy with respect to entropy at constant volume and constant number of particles in the system:\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nT = ((del U)/(del S))_(V,N)\n++++\n\nwhere stem:[U] is internal energy (<<t5-20.2>>), stem:[S] is entropy (<<t5-18>>), stem:[V] is volume (<<iso80000-3>>), and stem:[N] is number of particles\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "It is measured with a primary thermometer, examples of which are gas thermometers of different kinds, noise thermometers, or radiation thermometers.\n\nThe Boltzmann constant (<<iso80000-1>>) relates energy at the individual particle level with thermodynamic temperature.\n\nDifferences of thermodynamic temperatures or changes may be expressed either in kelvin, symbol stem:[\"unitsml(K)\"], or in de grees Celsius, symbol stem:[\"unitsml(degC)\"] (<<t5-2>>).\n\nThermodynamic temperature is one of the seven base quantities in the International System of Quantities, ISQ (see <<iso80000-1>>).\n\n*The International Temperature Scale of 1990*\n\nFor the purpose of practical measurements, the International Temperature Scale of 1990, ITS-90, was adopted by CIPM in 1989, which is a close approximation to the thermodynamic temperature scale.\n\nThe quantities defined by this scale are denoted stem:[T_\"90\"] and stem:[t_\"90\"], respectively (replacing stem:[T_\"68\"] and stem:[t_\"68\"] defined by the International Practical Temperature Scale of 1968, IPTS-68), where\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\n(t_\"90\")/(1 \"unitsml(degC)\") = (T_\"90\")/(1 \"unitsml(K)\") - 273.15\n++++\n\nThe units of stem:[T_\"90\"] and stem:[t_\"90\"] are the kelvin, symbol stem:[\"unitsml(K)\"], and the degree Celsius, symbol stem:[\"unitsml(degC)\"] (<<t5-2>>), respectively.\n\nFor further information, see <<its90>>, <<mepkelvin>>.\n\nFor ready conversion between temperatures reported on the International Temperature Scale and thermodynamic temperatures the systematic deviations can be found in <<estimates>>.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-K"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-5"
      }
    }
  ]
